Package tp.pr4

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    City
    This class represents the city where the robot is wandering.
    Interpreter
    The interpreter is in charge of converting the user input in an instruction for the robot.
    Main
    Application entry-point.
    NavigationModule
    This class is in charge of the robot navigation features.
    Place
    It represents a place in the city.
    RobotEngine
    This class represents the robot engine.
    Street
    A street links two places A and B in one direction.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Direction
    An enumerated type that represents the compass directions (north, east, south and west) plus a value that represents an unknown direction.
    Rotation
    An enum class that represents in which direction the robot rotates (left or right) plus a value that represents an unknown direction.
